name: Justo Suárez
description: Justo Suárez was one of the first popular boxers in Argentina. Known as “El torito de Mataderos”, he grew up with 25 brothers and sisters in a house in Guaminí Street. He came straight from nothing and became quickly famous. He only lost two fights, but a strong tuberculosis weakened him and left him poor and jobless. Three years later he died at 29. Cortázar wrote a tale dedicated to him called Torito.
